 Productivity Suite Documentation
A complete guide to using, understanding, and extending the Python Productivity Suite, which integrates multiple tools (Calculator, Notes Manager, Timer, File Organizer) using object-oriented design, modular architecture, and clean file handling.

 1. Introduction
The Productivity Suite is a modular Python-based application that brings together essential productivity tools in a simple command-line interface. It is designed with:
•	Clean OOP structure
•	Easy-to-maintain module separation
•	Efficient file handling for notes and organizing files
•	A user-friendly CLI menu
•	Expandable architecture for adding more tools in the future
This documentation provides:
•	Tool descriptions
•	Usage instructions
•	Architecture overview
•	Developer notes
•	Example commands and outputs

 2. Features Overview
Calculator Tool
•	Supports Add, Subtract, Multiply, Divide
•	Handles invalid inputs and zero-division errors
Notes Manager Tool
•	Create, view, list, edit, delete notes
•	Notes stored under data/notes/
•	File-based management (TXT or JSON)

Timer & Stopwatch Tool
•	Start, pause, resume, stop stopwatch
•	Countdown timer support
•	Tracks elapsed time with precision
File Organizer Tool
•	Automatically organizes files by type
•	Moves files into Images, Documents, Videos, Audio, Others
•	Uses safe file handling with overwrite protection

