4. Installation Guide
Step 1: Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/productivity-suite.git
cd productivity-suite
Step 2: Create Virtual Environment (Optional but Recommended)
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Linux / macOS
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows
Step 3: Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

 5. Running the Application
Run the main entry point:
python main.py
The main menu will appear:
==========================================
        PERSONAL PRODUCTIVITY SUITE
==========================================
1. Calculator
2. Notes Manager
3. Timer & Stopwatch
4. File Organizer
5. Unit Converter
6. Backup & Restore
7. Exit
Enter your choice:

 6. Calculator Module
Location: modules/calculator.py
Class: Calculator
Available Operations:
•	add(a, b)
•	subtract(a, b)
•	multiply(a, b)
•	divide(a, b)
Example:
from modules.calculator import Calculator
calc = Calculator()
print(calc.add(5, 3))  # Output: 8

 7. Notes Manager Module
Location: modules/notes.py
Class: NotesManager
Features:
•	Create new note
•	List existing notes
•	Read note content
•	Edit a note
•	Delete a note
•	Search notes

Example:
from modules.notes import NotesManager
nm = NotesManager("data/notes")
nm.create("Shopping List", "Milk, Eggs, Bread")

 8. Timer & Stopwatch Module
Location: modules/timer.py
Class: Timer
Functions:
•	start()
•	pause()
•	resume()
•	stop()
•	elapsed_time()
Example:
from modules.timer import Timer
sw = Timer()
sw.start()
# ...task...
sw.stop()
print(sw.elapsed_time())

 9. File Organizer Module
Location: modules/file_organizer.py
Class: FileOrganizer
Features:
•	Automatically organizes files
•	Categorizes by file type
•	Moves files safely into subfolders
•	Supports customizable file-type mappings

Example:
from modules.file_organizer import FileOrganizer
fo = FileOrganizer()
fo.organize("C:/Users/Downloads")

 10. Running Unit Tests
Run all tests using:
python -m unittest discover -s tests
Test files include:
•	test_calculator.py
•	test_notes.py
•	test_file_organizer.py

 11. Architecture & Design Principles
1. Object-Oriented Design
Each tool is encapsulated in its own class.
2. Separation of Concerns
•	UI is handled in Main.py
•	Logic stays inside modules/
3. File Handling Safety
•	Notes stored with timestamps
•	File Organizer checks for folder existence
•	Uses .gitkeep to maintain empty directories
4. Expandability
New modules can be added easily (e.g., reminders, password manager, to-do list).

 12. Future Enhancements
•	GUI using Tkinter or PyQt
•	Cloud backup for notes
•	File organizer with duplicate detection
•	Auto-save notes
•	Voice-enabled timer

